CatDescriptText: Cutline of images published in Pittsburgh Courier Newspaper, September 10, 1960, pg. A2 reads: "Top Newsboys Win Top Prizes - The smiling faces of Courier newsboy prize-winners were quite evident at the annual picnic last Friday in South Park.  These boys received sports equipment, consisting of footballs, basketballs, ping pong and badminton sets, baseballs, bats and gloves."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of young man wearing plaid short sleeve button down collared shirt, standing in front of trees in South Park for Pittsburgh Courier newsboys picnic; Portrait of boy wearing short sleeve button down collared shirt with jug and sun pattern, holding baseball bat, standing in front of tree in South Park for Pittsburgh Courier newsboys picnic
